cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper discusses a framework for synchronizing collections of changing Web resources, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of XML sitemaps and integration with the Web architecture suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. The focus on consistency, latency, and data transfer efficiency suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also relevant. The use of ad hoc or proprietary synchronization solutions suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may be relevant as well. Finally, the experiments and simulations described in the paper suggest that cs.SE (Software Engineering) may also be relevant.
